metadata.name: Atoms' Gaze #261
metadata.description:
How the lives of many affect the whole.

A holistic exploration of the growth of crystalline structures. Discovering the complexity of natural forms built from the simple rules of a deterministic system. What choice do individuals have but to be part of the story?

As microscopic particles interact and coalesce they form the macrocosm. The path they take however, is only known once it is complete. Along the way they may encounter many or none at all; each instance defining its past and future. The only knowns are that this will be the only path they take and that it'll always end.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image by ***double clicking/tapping***

Features include: palette, foreground and background structures, particle rules, number of particles, colour displacement and noise.

Created on Chrome desktop 100.0 on 2022-04-16. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Shadow Blocks - RGBDL #16
metadata.description:
Interactive 3D sculpture.

Three directional lights (Red, Green and Blue) are aimed to a canvas filled with randomly positioned blocks. Each light brightens the canvas and projects shadows behind each block. Other three colors (Yellow, Magenta and Cyan) emerge because of the additive property of light.

Shadow Blocks was created inspired by the sculptures made by Charles Biederman (see _Structurist Relief, Red Wing Number 1_, 1958) and the exploration of light by Olafur Eliasson (see _Your uncertain shadow (colour), 2010_).

by @code2pixels
February, 2022

Made with three.js

Shadow Blocks © 2022 by code2pixels is licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

--------------------------------------------------------------

FEATURES
- Blocks Orientation
	- Vertical ~ 10%
	- Horizontal ~ 10%
	- Perpendicular ~ 80%
- Light Direction
	- Perpendicular ~ 10%
	- Vertical ~ 10% 
	- Horizontal ~ 10%
	- All Directions ~ 70%

FUNCTIONALITIES
- Home Camera
	- Press 'h' to return camera to it's default position
- Toggle Lights
	- Press 'r', 'g' or 'b' to toggle on and off each light
	- Press 'a' to turn on all lights

metadata.description:

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.description:
Ripples - Made by Zoltan Szalay @insgraphizm with P5.js
April 2022, Hungary

Features
--------
7 color themes
Light or Dark background
Number of rings
Detail of noise

Keyboard control
----------------
[f] toggle fullscreen and hide cursor
[space] manually generate new composition
[a] automatically generate new composition
[s] save image

Touchscreen
-----------
Tap left edge to automatically or right edge to manually generate a new composition.

metadata.name: White Poppy 30 #34
metadata.description: 30-degree variations of a White Poppy.. The flower was 3D scanned, producing a 15 millions vertices point cloud. The point cloud was then simplified to 350k vertices, in order to be used here. This piece can still be a bit resource intensive. You can click/tap (or press 's') to stop the spinning, this should help if your device is struggling - @smallfly

metadata.name: GOLENS #126
metadata.description:
"- May every star in the sky become a life?"
"- Yes, and I'll call them golens!

Have you ever noticed how morbid it is? People make wishes to shooting stars. Do they not understand? What can a star, desperate, in the midst of a suicidal fall, give you? She just wants to die at ocean.

Tonight the stars will not fall, they will rise, and they'll be watching our end, we'll die in the ocean.


GOLENS are generative created.
- 15 Body Parts ( not on traits )
- 6 Hierarchy Grades.
- 9 Sky.
- 4 Weathers.
- 9 Powers.


by Gen Doodler | twitter.com/GenDoodler
